<promed@promedmail.org>
[The question of how the virus may have come to the Ecuadorian shores from
Asia is similar to the question of how cholera reached the Peruvian shores
back in 1991. Speculation in 1991 was that ships from Asia may have emptied
their bilges near the coast, causing contamination of fish, crustaceans and
bivalves harvested from the waters. A similar scenario may account for the
introduction of the white spot virus. - MPP
